/exclusion criteria, as well as procedures for all stages of your review. This information can be included in various sections of your DMP.</span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3549,"created_at":"2021-06-04 16:53:45 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-04 16:53:45 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"0d1d139e-4ede-49ee-8281-556793a533a5"},{"id":3546,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3550,"created_at":"2021-06-07 18:49:14 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-07 18:49:14 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3547,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3551,"created_at":"2021-06-07 19:12:35 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-07 19:12:35 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3548,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3552,"created_at":"2021-06-07 19:15:20 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-07 19:15:20 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3549,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3553,"created_at":"2021-06-07 19:18:05 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-07 19:18:05 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3550,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3554,"created_at":"2021-06-07 19:27:27 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-07 19:27:27 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3551,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3555,"created_at":"2021-06-07 20:06:58 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-07 20:06:58 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3552,"title":"CRDCN Template for Accessing Data from Research Data Centres","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This template is for researchers who are doing RDC work using Statistics Canada data available in the RDC </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">only</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (i.e. there is no supplemental data, public use statistics, or any other information that complements the RDC work). If your work is being conducted in the RDC in concert with other data that you either intend to bring into the RDC or work on outside the RDC in parallel to your RDC work, then the RDC and External Analysis template should be completed.&nbsp;</span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3556,"created_at":"2021-06-07 20:08:11 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-07 20:08:11 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"3d9e83e3-cfa8-463b-84a1-78bb0d7ba287"},{"id":3553,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3557,"created_at":"2021-06-07 20:08:28 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-07 20:08:28 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3554,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3558,"created_at":"2021-06-07 20:12:43 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-07 20:12:43 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3555,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3559,"created_at":"2021-06-07 22:26:37 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-07 22:26:37 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3556,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3560,"created_at":"2021-06-08 01:02:45 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-08 01:02:45 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3557,"title":"Portage Template for Mixed Methods (Surveys & Qualitative Research)","description":"<p>This mixed methods data management plan template was developed for use within the Portage DMP Assistant and is meant to assist researchers conducting mixed methods research (e.g., surveys and qualitative interviews/focus groups) in developing high quality data management plans to support their research. The template consists of a number of categories, questions, and customized guidance that relate directly to mixed methods research.</p>","number":1,"template_id":3561,"created_at":"2021-06-08 14:33:30 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-08 14:33:30 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"1945d993-f3da-4a84-ad7f-ae2560946956"},{"id":3558,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3562,"created_at":"2021-06-08 16:57:26 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-08 16:57:26 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3559,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3563,"created_at":"2021-06-08 18:41:25 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-08 18:41:25 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3560,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3565,"created_at":"2021-06-09 15:38:04 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-09 15:38:04 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3561,"title":"Portage Template for Qualitative Health Sciences Research","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This data management template is meant to be used by health sciences researchers conducting qualitative research on human subjects. It includes guidance on data management best practices beginning with data collection through to data sharing.</span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3566,"created_at":"2021-06-10 00:29:56 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-10 00:29:56 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"012fd11d-1c7c-424c-a883-6134132b8a82"},{"id":3562,"title":"Phase 1: Data Preparation","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3567,"created_at":"2021-06-10 00:33:15 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-10 00:33:15 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"05d7f955-8c04-4752-9fae-2293a77b7c88"},{"id":3563,"title":"Phase 2: Active Research (Data) Management","description":null,"number":2,"template_id":3567,"created_at":"2021-06-10 00:33:15 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-10 00:33:15 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"4b54c857-03ae-486b-884b-1c90a2b4e4bc"},{"id":3564,"title":"Phase 3: Data Protection","description":null,"number":3,"template_id":3567,"created_at":"2021-06-10 00:33:16 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-10 00:33:16 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"3c4e5a7f-a13a-44e4-986d-0e61f4748e07"},{"id":3565,"title":"Phase 4: Sharing and Preserving","description":null,"number":4,"template_id":3567,"created_at":"2021-06-10 00:33:16 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-10 00:33:16 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"d1fd3a69-036b-4779-a768-3b05bc27ff1a"},{"id":3566,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3568,"created_at":"2021-06-10 00:33:47 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-10 00:33:47 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3567,"title":"Portage Template for Mixed Methods (Surveys & Qualitative Research)","description":"<p>This mixed methods data management plan template was developed for use within the Portage DMP Assistant and is meant to assist researchers conducting mixed methods research (e.g., surveys and qualitative interviews/focus groups) in developing high quality data management plans to support their research. The template consists of a number of categories, questions, and customized guidance that relate directly to mixed methods research.</p>","number":1,"template_id":3569,"created_at":"2021-06-10 00:45:17 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-10 00:45:17 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"1945d993-f3da-4a84-ad7f-ae2560946956"},{"id":3568,"title":"tester","description":"<p>tester</p>","number":1,"template_id":3570,"created_at":"2021-06-10 05:15:25 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-10 05:15:25 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"27823c59-c4cd-47cf-b35d-7fbf4f2962e8"},{"id":3569,"title":"tester2","description":"<p>tet</p>","number":1,"template_id":3571,"created_at":"2021-06-10 05:30:54 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-10 05:30:54 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"4e8f2154-4125-4a0b-9806-d1e4a93c8d2f"},{"id":3570,"title":"tester2","description":"<p>tet</p>","number":1,"template_id":3572,"created_at":"2021-06-10 15:50:07 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-10 15:50:07 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"4e8f2154-4125-4a0b-9806-d1e4a93c8d2f"},{"id":3571,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3573,"created_at":"2021-06-15 14:11:35 UTC","updated_at":"2021-06-15 14:11:35 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3572,"title":"U of T DMP Questions","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3574,"created_at":"2021-07-07 14:14:33 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-07 14:25:47 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"8182d4b7-4fcd-455b-b102-01ffe093d211"},{"id":3573,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3575,"created_at":"2021-07-07 14:21:37 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-07 14:21:37 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3575,"title":"Portage Template for Mixed Methods (Surveys & Qualitative Research)","description":"<p>This mixed methods data management plan template was developed for use within the Portage DMP Assistant and is meant to assist researchers conducting mixed methods research (e.g., surveys and qualitative interviews/focus groups) in developing high quality data management plans to support their research. The template consists of a number of categories, questions, and customized guidance that relate directly to mixed methods research.</p>","number":1,"template_id":3576,"created_at":"2021-07-09 13:51:47 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-09 13:51:47 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"1945d993-f3da-4a84-ad7f-ae2560946956"},{"id":3576,"title":"Portage Template for Qualitative Health Sciences Research","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This data management template is meant to be used by health sciences researchers conducting qualitative research on human subjects. It includes guidance on data management best practices beginning with data collection through to data sharing.</span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3577,"created_at":"2021-07-09 13:52:47 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-09 13:52:47 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"012fd11d-1c7c-424c-a883-6134132b8a82"},{"id":3577,"title":"Portage Template for Open Science Workflows","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This template guides the writing of a research data management plan (DMP) with an open science/open scholarship workflow, which uses mixed social sciences research methods, producing quantitative as well as qualitative datasets. The questions emphasize data sharing and reuse throughout the project, not only at the final stage of publication. This DMP template will be most useful to researchers who are working in a multi-institutional partnership and who have already completed a funding application and an ethics review protocol.&nbsp; The DMP is a living document:</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">don&rsquo;t forget to revisit your DMP throughout the research project to update or review your responses.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Not all of these questions will apply to all research projects. We encourage you to respond to as many as possible but ultimately, you and your team have to decide which questions and answers apply to your workflow. </span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3578,"created_at":"2021-07-09 13:53:45 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-09 13:53:45 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"e6951813-58f1-4b51-918d-5b29a744541d"},{"id":3578,"title":"Portage Template for Systematic Reviews","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This template provides general guidance for those who are undertaking systematic reviews. It is suggested that different team members contribute to the DMP based on the stage of the review process in which they will be involved in creating data.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For additional guidance and examples, please see the online research guide located at </span><a href=\"https://library.ucalgary.ca/dmpforsr\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">https://library.ucalgary.ca/dmpforsr</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The </span><a href=\"http://www.prisma-statement.org/Extensions/Protocols.aspx\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">PRISMA-P for systematic review protocols</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is a tool that may help with planning and describing your data management process. It requires you to specify which databases you&rsquo;ll search, present a draft search strategy, report your inclusion/exclusion criteria, as well as procedures for all stages of your review. This information can be included in various sections of your DMP.</span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3579,"created_at":"2021-07-09 13:54:23 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-09 13:54:23 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"0d1d139e-4ede-49ee-8281-556793a533a5"},{"id":3579,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3580,"created_at":"2021-07-09 13:55:20 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-09 13:55:20 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3580,"title":"Phase 1: Data Management Plan for Grant Application","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&ldquo;Phase 1&rdquo; is for the documentation of DMP sections joined with a funding application. The headings documented in Phase&nbsp;1 are primarily aimed at producing a DMP to support research data management (RDM) budgeting for the research project.</span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3581,"created_at":"2021-07-09 13:55:40 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-09 13:55:40 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"05204d86-fc3a-4e00-a791-4701dd5042db"},{"id":3581,"title":"Phase 2: Data Management Plan for Project Development","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&ldquo;Phase 2&rdquo; may be considered once funding has been secured. The entire DMP is an evolving management document since the content of certain headings will only become clearer once the project is well underway.</span></p>","number":2,"template_id":3581,"created_at":"2021-07-09 13:55:41 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-09 13:55:41 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"fce2cc8c-03bb-42b7-8e0e-471fb3d71a8e"},{"id":3582,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3582,"created_at":"2021-07-13 13:10:47 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-13 13:10:47 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3583,"title":"Write Plan","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3583,"created_at":"2021-07-15 20:03:24 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-15 20:48:49 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"d2cca033-9063-46e2-902f-af17abf1972b"},{"id":3586,"title":"Write Plan","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3584,"created_at":"2021-07-16 17:15:23 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-16 17:15:23 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"d2cca033-9063-46e2-902f-af17abf1972b"},{"id":3587,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3585,"created_at":"2021-07-20 18:29:14 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-20 18:29:14 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3588,"title":"Phase 1: Data Preparation","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3586,"created_at":"2021-07-21 17:11:20 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-21 17:11:20 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"05d7f955-8c04-4752-9fae-2293a77b7c88"},{"id":3589,"title":"Phase 2: Active Research (Data) Management","description":null,"number":2,"template_id":3586,"created_at":"2021-07-21 17:11:20 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-21 17:11:20 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"4b54c857-03ae-486b-884b-1c90a2b4e4bc"},{"id":3590,"title":"Phase 3: Data Protection","description":null,"number":3,"template_id":3586,"created_at":"2021-07-21 17:11:21 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-21 17:11:21 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"3c4e5a7f-a13a-44e4-986d-0e61f4748e07"},{"id":3591,"title":"Phase 4: Sharing and Preserving","description":null,"number":4,"template_id":3586,"created_at":"2021-07-21 17:11:21 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-21 17:11:21 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"d1fd3a69-036b-4779-a768-3b05bc27ff1a"},{"id":3592,"title":"CRDCN Template for Research Data Centres and External Analysis","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This template is for researchers who are doing RDC work using Statistics Canada data </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">and</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> research data that they have either brought into the RDC &ldquo;supplemental data&rdquo; or are analyzing in parallel to their work in the RDC (such as mixed-methods) or public use statistics that compliment the RDC work (hereafter: </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">external data</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">). Researchers should be aware that any data brought into the RDC will be stored alongside the rest of their project material subject to the information management protocols from Statistics Canada. This is a free, relatively straightforward, process and researchers can obtain more information by talking to their RDC analyst.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">If your work is being conducted in the RDC using only data provided through the RDC program then the RDC-only template should be completed and not this template.&nbsp;</span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3587,"created_at":"2021-07-21 17:15:20 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-21 17:15:20 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"38c1bf2b-d79f-4b4f-a17c-243ebcfb8d70"},{"id":3593,"title":"PGD UQTR","description":"<p>Ce mod&egrave;le de plan de gestion de donn&eacute;es est bas&eacute; sur le mod&egrave;le de Portage. Il comprend des exemples, directives et conseils destin&eacute;s aux chercheurs de l'UQTR.</p>\r\n<p>Comme il s'agit d'un mod&egrave;le de PGD multidisciplinaire servant de guide, certaines questions ne s'appliquent pas &agrave; tous les projets de recherche, le cas &eacute;ch&eacute;ant, inscrivez-y \"N/A\" en guise de r&eacute;ponse. Il est recommand&eacute; de commencer par lire toutes les questions du PGD afin d'&eacute;viter les redondances. Des mod&egrave;les sp&eacute;cifiques en lien avec diff&eacute;rents types de recherche ou diff&eacute;rentes disciplines sont &eacute;galement disponibles sous l'onglet <em>r&eacute;f&eacute;rence</em> plus haut, nous vous encourageons &agrave; les consulter afin d'enrichir votre PGD.</p>\r\n<p>Un PGD est un document qui &eacute;volue. Au cours du projet, il doit &ecirc;tre mis &agrave; jour selon les changements dans vos pratiques de gestion de donn&eacute;es.</p>\r\n<p>Pour de l'information g&eacute;n&eacute;rale et des conseils sur la gestion des donn&eacute;es de recherche (GDR), consultez le&nbsp;<a href=\"https://oraprdnt.uqtr.uquebec.ca/pls/public/gscw031?owa_no_site=874&amp;owa_no_fiche=68&amp;owa_bottin=\">guide &eacute;labor&eacute; par le Service de la biblioth&egrave;que </a>de l'Universit&eacute; du Qu&eacute;bec &agrave; Trois-Rivi&egrave;res.</p>\r\n<p>Pour toute question, vous pouvez contacter un professionnel &agrave;&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:gdr@uqtr.ca\">gdr@uqtr.ca</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Les exemples et conseils fournis sont tir&eacute;s du mat&eacute;riel produit par Portage (CC-BY) : <a href=\"https://portagenetwork.ca/fr/outils-et-ressources/ressources-de-formation-de-portage/\">https://portagenetwork.ca/fr/outils-et-ressources/ressources-de-formation-de-portage/</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","number":1,"template_id":3588,"created_at":"2021-07-21 17:23:05 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-21 17:23:05 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"1aed716c-e113-498d-86cc-ccb2f65f1f5a"},{"id":3594,"title":"CRDCN Template for Accessing Data from Research Data Centres","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This template is for researchers who are doing RDC work using Statistics Canada data available in the RDC </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">only</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (i.e. there is no supplemental data, public use statistics, or any other information that complements the RDC work). If your work is being conducted in the RDC in concert with other data that you either intend to bring into the RDC or work on outside the RDC in parallel to your RDC work, then the RDC and External Analysis template should be completed.&nbsp;</span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3589,"created_at":"2021-07-21 17:37:04 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-21 17:37:04 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"3d9e83e3-cfa8-463b-84a1-78bb0d7ba287"},{"id":3595,"title":"Portage Template for Mixed Methods (Surveys & Qualitative Research)","description":"<p>This mixed methods data management plan template was developed for use within the Portage DMP Assistant and is meant to assist researchers conducting mixed methods research (e.g., surveys and qualitative interviews/focus groups) in developing high quality data management plans to support their research. The template consists of a number of categories, questions, and customized guidance that relate directly to mixed methods research.</p>","number":1,"template_id":3590,"created_at":"2021-07-21 18:07:15 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-21 18:07:15 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"1945d993-f3da-4a84-ad7f-ae2560946956"},{"id":3596,"title":"Software/Technology Management Plan","description":"<p>This section <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">is focused solely on a management plan for the creation of software or technology.</span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3591,"created_at":"2021-07-21 18:08:40 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-21 18:08:40 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"0ef47415-b642-46c5-98c3-e4530c541b63"},{"id":3597,"title":"Data Management Plan","description":"<p>This section is focused <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">on a data management plan designed to describe the methods in which data are gathered, analyzed, and shared from participants based on interventions or testing of the corresponding software or technology</span></p>","number":2,"template_id":3591,"created_at":"2021-07-21 18:08:40 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-21 18:08:40 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"4e00645f-49e4-4c08-a074-1d06bab51dd2"},{"id":3598,"title":"PGD UQTR","description":"<p>Ce mod&egrave;le de plan de gestion de donn&eacute;es est bas&eacute; sur le mod&egrave;le de Portage. Il comprend des exemples, directives et conseils destin&eacute;s aux chercheurs de l'UQTR.</p>\r\n<p>Comme il s'agit d'un mod&egrave;le de PGD multidisciplinaire servant de guide, certaines questions ne s'appliquent pas &agrave; tous les projets de recherche, le cas &eacute;ch&eacute;ant, inscrivez-y \"N/A\" en guise de r&eacute;ponse. Il est recommand&eacute; de commencer par lire toutes les questions du PGD afin d'&eacute;viter les redondances. Des mod&egrave;les sp&eacute;cifiques en lien avec diff&eacute;rents types de recherche ou diff&eacute;rentes disciplines sont &eacute;galement disponibles sous l'onglet <em>R&eacute;f&eacute;rence</em> plus haut, nous vous encourageons &agrave; les consulter afin d'enrichir votre PGD.</p>\r\n<p>Un PGD est un document qui &eacute;volue. Au cours du projet, il doit &ecirc;tre mis &agrave; jour selon les changements dans vos pratiques de gestion de donn&eacute;es.</p>\r\n<p>Pour de l'information g&eacute;n&eacute;rale et des conseils sur la gestion des donn&eacute;es de recherche (GDR), consultez le&nbsp;<a href=\"https://oraprdnt.uqtr.uquebec.ca/pls/public/gscw031?owa_no_site=874&amp;owa_no_fiche=68&amp;owa_bottin=\">guide &eacute;labor&eacute; par le Service de la biblioth&egrave;que </a>de l'Universit&eacute; du Qu&eacute;bec &agrave; Trois-Rivi&egrave;res.</p>\r\n<p>Pour toute question, vous pouvez contacter un professionnel &agrave;&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:gdr@uqtr.ca\">gdr@uqtr.ca</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Les exemples et conseils fournis sont tir&eacute;s du mat&eacute;riel produit par Portage (CC-BY) : <a href=\"https://portagenetwork.ca/fr/outils-et-ressources/ressources-de-formation-de-portage/\">https://portagenetwork.ca/fr/outils-et-ressources/ressources-de-formation-de-portage/</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","number":1,"template_id":3592,"created_at":"2021-07-21 18:22:52 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-21 18:22:52 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"1aed716c-e113-498d-86cc-ccb2f65f1f5a"},{"id":3600,"title":"Project Initiating Data","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3596,"created_at":"2021-07-21 20:19:59 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-21 20:19:59 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"d2cca033-9063-46e2-902f-af17abf1972b"},{"id":3601,"title":"Collected Data","description":"","number":2,"template_id":3596,"created_at":"2021-07-21 20:20:00 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-21 20:20:00 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"1b278ed2-53c0-4885-913c-98625291402f"},{"id":3602,"title":"Derived Data","description":"","number":3,"template_id":3596,"created_at":"2021-07-21 20:20:01 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-21 20:20:01 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"7b48ee1f-9911-48ed-97b9-a691bbc8759c"},{"id":3603,"title":"Western DMP","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3595,"created_at":"2021-07-21 20:22:34 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-21 20:23:17 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"a1b1bf7d-4193-4c4b-88d7-7917e40bf003"},{"id":3604,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3597,"created_at":"2021-07-21 20:46:38 UTC","updated_at":"2021-07-21 20:46:38 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3605,"title":"Western DMP","desc