g Statistics Canada data available in the RDC </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">only</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (i.e. there is no supplemental data, public use statistics, or any other information that complements the RDC work). If your work is being conducted in the RDC in concert with other data that you either intend to bring into the RDC or work on outside the RDC in parallel to your RDC work, then the RDC and External Analysis template should be completed.&nbsp;</span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3616,"created_at":"2021-08-05 15:04:14 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-05 15:04:14 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"3d9e83e3-cfa8-463b-84a1-78bb0d7ba287"},{"id":3628,"title":"CRDCN Template for Accessing Data from Research Data Centres","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This template is for researchers who are doing RDC work using Statistics Canada data available in the RDC </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">only</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (i.e. there is no supplemental data, public use statistics, or any other information that complements the RDC work). If your work is being conducted in the RDC in concert with other data that you either intend to bring into the RDC or work on outside the RDC in parallel to your RDC work, then the RDC and External Analysis template should be completed.&nbsp;</span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3617,"created_at":"2021-08-05 15:11:17 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-05 15:11:17 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"3d9e83e3-cfa8-463b-84a1-78bb0d7ba287"},{"id":3629,"title":"Project Initiating Data","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3618,"created_at":"2021-08-13 18:49:37 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-13 18:49:37 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"d2cca033-9063-46e2-902f-af17abf1972b"},{"id":3630,"title":"Collected Data","description":"","number":2,"template_id":3618,"created_at":"2021-08-13 18:49:38 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-13 18:49:38 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"1b278ed2-53c0-4885-913c-98625291402f"},{"id":3631,"title":"Derived Data","description":"","number":3,"template_id":3618,"created_at":"2021-08-13 18:49:39 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-13 18:49:39 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"7b48ee1f-9911-48ed-97b9-a691bbc8759c"},{"id":3632,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3619,"created_at":"2021-08-18 14:40:42 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-18 14:40:42 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3633,"title":"Adaptation UL des questions du modle Portage","description":"<p>L'ensemble des points couverts par le mod&egrave;le Portage de base sont repris en leur ajoutant des ressources locales pour aider &agrave; r&eacute;pondre.</p>","number":1,"template_id":3620,"created_at":"2021-08-18 14:50:40 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-22 14:22:10 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"2b650b22-8a2b-4e80-a1a0-cf78df12c8d1"},{"id":3634,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3621,"created_at":"2021-08-23 17:12:40 UTC","updated_at":"2021-08-23 17:12:40 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3635,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3622,"created_at":"2021-09-21 16:39:10 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-21 16:39:10 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3636,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3623,"created_at":"2021-09-27 20:44:22 UTC","updated_at":"2021-09-27 20:44:22 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3637,"title":"Phase 1: Data Preparation","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3624,"created_at":"2021-10-04 15:44:14 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-04 15:44:14 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"05d7f955-8c04-4752-9fae-2293a77b7c88"},{"id":3638,"title":"Phase 2: Active Research (Data) Management","description":null,"number":2,"template_id":3624,"created_at":"2021-10-04 15:44:15 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-04 15:44:15 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"4b54c857-03ae-486b-884b-1c90a2b4e4bc"},{"id":3639,"title":"Phase 3: Data Protection","description":null,"number":3,"template_id":3624,"created_at":"2021-10-04 15:44:15 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-04 15:44:15 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"3c4e5a7f-a13a-44e4-986d-0e61f4748e07"},{"id":3640,"title":"Phase 4: Sharing and Preserving","description":null,"number":4,"template_id":3624,"created_at":"2021-10-04 15:44:15 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-04 15:44:15 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"d1fd3a69-036b-4779-a768-3b05bc27ff1a"},{"id":3641,"title":"Portage Template for Arts-Based Research","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This template will assist you in creating a data management plan for arts-based research (ABR). It is intended for researchers and artists who use artistic processes as research methods (i.e., arts-based methods). ABR is used across disciplines and encompasses diverse understandings of the arts, research, and how they intersect. In this template, ABR is an umbrella term for all the ways the arts are adapted to answer research questions, including those described as arts research, artistic research, and research-creation. You can use this template on its own, or in combination with others on the </span><a href=\"https://assistant.portagenetwork.ca/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">DMP Assistant</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> when using arts-based methods with other methodological approaches. </span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3625,"created_at":"2021-10-04 15:50:23 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-04 15:50:23 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"5ba3ad08-b91a-4194-8d20-d904b09fa950"},{"id":3642,"title":"Portage Template for Open Science Workflows","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This template guides the writing of a research data management plan (DMP) with an open science/open scholarship workflow, which uses mixed social sciences research methods, producing quantitative as well as qualitative datasets. The questions emphasize data sharing and reuse throughout the project, not only at the final stage of publication. This DMP template will be most useful to researchers who are working in a multi-institutional partnership and who have already completed a funding application and an ethics review protocol.&nbsp; The DMP is a living document:</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">don&rsquo;t forget to revisit your DMP throughout the research project to update or review your responses.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Not all of these questions will apply to all research projects. We encourage you to respond to as many as possible but ultimately, you and your team have to decide which questions and answers apply to your workflow. </span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3626,"created_at":"2021-10-04 15:50:40 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-04 15:50:40 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"e6951813-58f1-4b51-918d-5b29a744541d"},{"id":3643,"title":"Phase 1","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Phase 1 questions probe at a high-level, seeking information about the general direction of the study. Normally, researchers will be able to respond to phase 1 questions at the outset of a project.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3627,"created_at":"2021-10-04 15:50:57 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-04 15:50:57 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"c5dbdb42-b148-4fb4-bba1-c6b3e435f4e6"},{"id":3644,"title":"Phase 2","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Phase 2 questions seek greater detail. It is understood that these answers will often depend on the outcome of several steps in the research project, such as: a literature review, imaging protocol design and experimental design, or running multiple pilot subjects and interpreting the outcome. As these details become known, the DMP can and should be revisited. This approach underscores that DMPs are living documents that evolve throughout a research project.&nbsp; </span></p>","number":2,"template_id":3627,"created_at":"2021-10-04 15:50:57 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-04 15:50:57 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"82eae2ac-d34d-4509-9dc6-e760741d253a"},{"id":3645,"title":"Portage Template for Studying Molecular Interactions","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The following template is intended for research projects combining experimental (scientific) methods with computer modeling/simulation to study molecular interactions. </span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3628,"created_at":"2021-10-04 15:51:12 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-04 15:51:12 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"6ab2d2c7-c1d4-4379-b478-c8edfab0e98e"},{"id":3646,"title":"Portage Template for Mixed Methods (Surveys & Qualitative Research)","description":"<p>This mixed methods data management plan template was developed for use within the Portage DMP Assistant and is meant to assist researchers conducting mixed methods research (e.g., surveys and qualitative interviews/focus groups) in developing high quality data management plans to support their research. The template consists of a number of categories, questions, and customized guidance that relate directly to mixed methods research.</p>","number":1,"template_id":3629,"created_at":"2021-10-04 19:09:59 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-04 19:09:59 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"1945d993-f3da-4a84-ad7f-ae2560946956"},{"id":3647,"title":"Portage Template for Systematic Reviews","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This template provides general guidance for those who are undertaking systematic reviews. It is suggested that different team members contribute to the DMP based on the stage of the review process in which they will be involved in creating data.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">For additional guidance and examples, please see the online research guide located at </span><a href=\"https://library.ucalgary.ca/dmpforsr\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">https://library.ucalgary.ca/dmpforsr</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The </span><a href=\"http://www.prisma-statement.org/Extensions/Protocols.aspx\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">PRISMA-P for systematic review protocols</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> is a tool that may help with planning and describing your data management process. It requires you to specify which databases you&rsquo;ll search, present a draft search strategy, report your inclusion/exclusion criteria, as well as procedures for all stages of your review. This information can be included in various sections of your DMP.</span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3630,"created_at":"2021-10-05 18:22:52 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-05 18:22:52 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"0d1d139e-4ede-49ee-8281-556793a533a5"},{"id":3648,"title":"Donnes initiales","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3631,"created_at":"2021-10-05 20:32:53 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-05 20:32:53 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"0fe204ed-a8b9-4842-bf6f-b0ee9378698d"},{"id":3649,"title":"Donnes collectes","description":"","number":2,"template_id":3631,"created_at":"2021-10-06 13:37:05 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-06 13:37:05 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"94c9667c-3666-4792-a551-dae3000d4361"},{"id":3650,"title":"Donnes drives","description":"","number":3,"template_id":3631,"created_at":"2021-10-06 15:31:08 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-19 19:30:12 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"5d6717a3-2115-40ad-aea4-0565c8def570"},{"id":3653,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3634,"created_at":"2021-10-06 19:41:37 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-06 19:41:37 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3654,"title":"Questions","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3635,"created_at":"2021-10-08 19:25:33 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-08 19:25:33 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"5680a543-3029-4a3b-875c-b40321a70779"},{"id":3656,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3637,"created_at":"2021-10-13 19:41:50 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-13 19:41:50 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3657,"title":"Phase 1: Data Preparation","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3638,"created_at":"2021-10-21 13:23:43 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-21 13:23:43 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"05d7f955-8c04-4752-9fae-2293a77b7c88"},{"id":3658,"title":"Phase 2: Active Research (Data) Management","description":null,"number":2,"template_id":3638,"created_at":"2021-10-21 13:23:43 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-21 13:23:43 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"4b54c857-03ae-486b-884b-1c90a2b4e4bc"},{"id":3659,"title":"Phase 3: Data Protection","description":null,"number":3,"template_id":3638,"created_at":"2021-10-21 13:23:43 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-21 13:23:43 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"3c4e5a7f-a13a-44e4-986d-0e61f4748e07"},{"id":3660,"title":"Phase 4: Sharing and Preserving","description":null,"number":4,"template_id":3638,"created_at":"2021-10-21 13:23:43 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-21 13:23:43 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"d1fd3a69-036b-4779-a768-3b05bc27ff1a"},{"id":3661,"title":"Alliance/Food from Thought DMP creation","description":"<p>This is the template to use when developing a DMP as a requirement for Alliance and Food from Thought funding.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Public Access to Your DMP</strong></p>\r\n<p>Increasing access and sharing of information is important for facilitating new agri-food and rural research and data analytics to inform decision-making. As such, the contents of this DMP may be made public. By completing this DMP, you are acknowledging that this information may be shared publicly. If you feel any information in your DMP should not be shared, please enter it in the \"confidential information\" section. If you have any concerns please contact the U of G Library at <a href=\"mailto:lib.research@uoguelph.ca\">lib.research@uoguelph.ca</a>.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Living Document</strong></p>\r\n<p>In most cases, DMPs are a condition of award. That said, DMPs are a living document that can be adjusted as necessary throughout the lifecycle of the project. Researchers are required to provide funders with updated information about their DMP if there are any changes. For Alliance projects, researchers are required to describe how the Data Management Plan has been implemented (if applicable) and if there any deviations from the proposed plan in the final report.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Clarity, Brevity and Accessibility</strong></p>\r\n<p>Please make your responses as clear and succinct as possible. For better accessibility, please avoid the use of tables.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Plan Details</strong></p>\r\n<p>On the previous tab, please ensure that you completed the fields as follows.</p>\r\n<p><em>Funder:</em> This should be either \"Ontario Agri-Food Innovation Alliance\" or \"Food from Thought.\"</p>\r\n<p><em>Grant Number:</em> This should be your Submission Number (e.g. UG-TI-2021-100000) and NOT the FRS Number.</p>\r\n<p><em>Project Abstract:</em> This can be copied and pasted from your application.</p>\r\n<p><em>ID:</em>&nbsp;This field is not relevant and does not need to be completed.</p>\r\n<p><strong>DMP Questions</strong></p>\r\n<p>Below is an overview of the questions you will need to address to complete your DMP. Click the \"Write Plan\" tab to begin responding to the questions.</p>","number":1,"template_id":3639,"created_at":"2021-10-27 19:14:02 UTC","updated_at":"2021-10-27 19:14:02 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"4189ab22-ee4a-4563-8e2e-2016f60969ba"},{"id":3662,"title":"York U Data Management Questions","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3640,"created_at":"2021-11-04 20:12:29 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-04 20:12:29 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"d15e450d-2ec4-432c-97d1-315d4af5b367"},{"id":3663,"title":"York U Data Management Questions","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3641,"created_at":"2021-11-04 21:36:12 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-04 21:36:12 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"d15e450d-2ec4-432c-97d1-315d4af5b367"},{"id":3664,"title":"York U Data Management Questions","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3642,"created_at":"2021-11-04 21:39:40 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-04 21:39:40 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"d15e450d-2ec4-432c-97d1-315d4af5b367"},{"id":3666,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3644,"created_at":"2021-11-04 22:03:05 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-04 22:03:05 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3667,"title":"Portage Template for Mixed Methods (Surveys & Qualitative Research)","description":"<p>This mixed methods data management plan template was developed for use within the Portage DMP Assistant and is meant to assist researchers conducting mixed methods research (e.g., surveys and qualitative interviews/focus groups) in developing high quality data management plans to support their research. The template consists of a number of categories, questions, and customized guidance that relate directly to mixed methods research.</p>","number":1,"template_id":3645,"created_at":"2021-11-05 17:24:42 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-05 17:24:42 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"1945d993-f3da-4a84-ad7f-ae2560946956"},{"id":3669,"title":"CRDCN Template for Accessing Data from Research Data Centres","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This template is for researchers who are doing RDC work using Statistics Canada data available in the RDC </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">only</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (i.e. there is no supplemental data, public use statistics, or any other information that complements the RDC work). If your work is being conducted in the RDC in concert with other data that you either intend to bring into the RDC or work on outside the RDC in parallel to your RDC work, then the RDC and External Analysis template should be completed.&nbsp;</span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3648,"created_at":"2021-11-12 19:58:37 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-12 19:58:37 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"3d9e83e3-cfa8-463b-84a1-78bb0d7ba287"},{"id":3670,"title":"Questions","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3649,"created_at":"2021-11-16 14:52:37 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-16 14:52:37 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"5680a543-3029-4a3b-875c-b40321a70779"},{"id":3671,"title":"Questions","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3650,"created_at":"2021-11-16 21:37:31 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-16 21:37:31 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"5680a543-3029-4a3b-875c-b40321a70779"},{"id":3672,"title":"Data Management","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3651,"created_at":"2021-11-17 19:05:56 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-19 19:09:15 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"0050a63b-e77a-460e-91da-0032cdd3fcd1"},{"id":3673,"title":"Questions","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3652,"created_at":"2021-11-18 15:31:06 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-18 15:31:06 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"5680a543-3029-4a3b-875c-b40321a70779"},{"id":3674,"title":"Questions","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3653,"created_at":"2021-11-18 15:38:40 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-18 15:38:40 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"5680a543-3029-4a3b-875c-b40321a70779"},{"id":3675,"title":"Questions","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3654,"created_at":"2021-11-18 16:05:22 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-18 16:05:22 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"5680a543-3029-4a3b-875c-b40321a70779"},{"id":3676,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3655,"created_at":"2021-11-24 15:34:15 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-24 15:34:15 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3677,"title":"TS Questions","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3656,"created_at":"2021-11-24 15:39:24 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-17 20:32:21 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"dd274118-dd77-4333-aeea-1af22ab08e03"},{"id":3678,"title":"Portage Template for Open Science Workflows","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This template guides the writing of a research data management plan (DMP) with an open science/open scholarship workflow, which uses mixed social sciences research methods, producing quantitative as well as qualitative datasets. The questions emphasize data sharing and reuse throughout the project, not only at the final stage of publication. This DMP template will be most useful to researchers who are working in a multi-institutional partnership and who have already completed a funding application and an ethics review protocol.&nbsp; The DMP is a living document:</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">don&rsquo;t forget to revisit your DMP throughout the research project to update or review your responses.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Not all of these questions will apply to all research projects. We encourage you to respond to as many as possible but ultimately, you and your team have to decide which questions and answers apply to your workflow. </span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3657,"created_at":"2021-11-24 19:51:25 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-24 19:51:25 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"e6951813-58f1-4b51-918d-5b29a744541d"},{"id":3679,"title":"Software/Technology Management Plan","description":"<p>This section <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">is focused solely on a management plan for the creation of software or technology.</span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3658,"created_at":"2021-11-25 19:27:44 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-25 19:27:44 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"0ef47415-b642-46c5-98c3-e4530c541b63"},{"id":3680,"title":"Data Management Plan","description":"<p>This section is focused <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">on a data management plan designed to describe the methods in which data are gathered, analyzed, and shared from participants based on interventions or testing of the corresponding software or technology</span></p>","number":2,"template_id":3658,"created_at":"2021-11-25 19:27:45 UTC","updated_at":"2021-11-25 19:27:45 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"4e00645f-49e4-4c08-a074-1d06bab51dd2"},{"id":3681,"title":"Western University ","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3659,"created_at":"2022-01-20 00:52:35 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-20 20:28:42 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"a1b1bf7d-4193-4c4b-88d7-7917e40bf003"},{"id":3682,"title":"Phase 1: Data Preparation","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3660,"created_at":"2022-01-27 15:16:40 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-27 15:16:40 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"05d7f955-8c04-4752-9fae-2293a77b7c88"},{"id":3683,"title":"Phase 2: Active Research (Data) Management","description":null,"number":2,"template_id":3660,"created_at":"2022-01-27 15:16:40 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-27 15:16:40 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"4b54c857-03ae-486b-884b-1c90a2b4e4bc"},{"id":3684,"title":"Phase 3: Data Protection","description":null,"number":3,"template_id":3660,"created_at":"2022-01-27 15:16:40 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-27 15:16:40 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"3c4e5a7f-a13a-44e4-986d-0e61f4748e07"},{"id":3685,"title":"Phase 4: Sharing and Preserving","description":null,"number":4,"template_id":3660,"created_at":"2022-01-27 15:16:40 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-27 15:16:40 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"d1fd3a69-036b-4779-a768-3b05bc27ff1a"},{"id":3686,"title":"Portage Template for Arts-Based Research","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This template will assist you in creating a data management plan for arts-based research (ABR). It is intended for researchers and artists who use artistic processes as research methods (i.e., arts-based methods). ABR is used across disciplines and encompasses diverse understandings of the arts, research, and how they intersect. In this template, ABR is an umbrella term for all the ways the arts are adapted to answer research questions, including those described as arts research, artistic research, and research-creation. You can use this template on its own, or in combination with others on the </span><a href=\"https://assistant.portagenetwork.ca/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">DMP Assistant</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> when using arts-based methods with other methodological approaches. </span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3661,"created_at":"2022-01-28 16:29:52 UTC","updated_at":"2022-01-28 16:29:52 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"5ba3ad08-b91a-4194-8d20-d904b09fa950"},{"id":3689,"title":"Portage Template for Water Quality Research","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This template provides guidance to researchers who are collecting or generating water quality data. Highly Qualified Personnel (HQP) and students are encouraged to consult with their advisors or principal investigators while completing this template. </span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3663,"created_at":"2022-02-04 15:39:21 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-04 15:39:21 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"cfd0d847-711a-44cf-8ee8-ac444142777d"},{"id":3690,"title":"Portage Template for Qualitative Health Sciences Research","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This data management template is meant to be used by health sciences researchers conducting qualitative research on human subjects. It includes guidance on data management best practices beginning with data collection through to data sharing.</span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3665,"created_at":"2022-02-17 15:01:39 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-17 15:01:39 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"012fd11d-1c7c-424c-a883-6134132b8a82"},{"id":3691,"title":"Alliance/Food from Thought DMP creation","description":"<p>This is the template to use when developing a DMP as a requirement for Alliance and Food from Thought funding.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Public Access to Your DMP</strong></p>\r\n<p>Increasing access and sharing of information is important for facilitating new agri-food and rural research and data analytics to inform decision-making. As such, the contents of this DMP may be made public. By completing this DMP, you are acknowledging that this information may be shared publicly. If you have any concerns please contact the U of G Library at <a href=\"mailto:lib.research@uoguelph.ca\">lib.research@uoguelph.ca</a>.</p>\r\n<p><strong>OMAFRA access to project data&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>As a recipient of funding through the Ontario Agri-Food Innovation Alliance, the Ontario Ministry of Agriculture, Food and Rural Affairs (OMAFRA) is entitled to request and be granted access to project data, including third-party data. Please contact Stacy Favrin, Senior Manager, OMAFRA/UofG Research Programs (<a href=\"mailto:favrinst@uoguelph.ca\">favrinst@uoguelph.ca</a>)&nbsp;for guidance before entering into a third-party agreement that may limit the Ministry's right to access data generated as part of this project.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Living Document</strong></p>\r\n<p>In most cases, DMPs are a condition of award. That said, DMPs are a living document that can be adjusted as necessary throughout the lifecycle of the project. Researchers are required to provide funders with updated information about their DMP if there are any changes. For Alliance projects, researchers are required to describe how the Data Management Plan has been implemented (if applicable) and if there any deviations from the proposed plan in the final report.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Clarity, Brevity and Accessibility</strong></p>\r\n<p>Please make your responses as clear and succinct as possible. For better accessibility, please avoid the use of tables.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Plan Details</strong></p>\r\n<p>On the previous tab, please ensure that you completed the fields as follows.</p>\r\n<p><em>Funder:</em> This should be either \"Ontario Agri-Food Innovation Alliance\" or \"Food from Thought.\"</p>\r\n<p><em>Grant Number:</em> This should be your Submission Number (e.g. UG-TI-2021-100000) and NOT the FRS Number.</p>\r\n<p><em>Project Abstract:</em> This can be copied and pasted from your application.</p>\r\n<p><em>ID:</em>&nbsp;This field is not relevant and does not need to be completed.</p>\r\n<p><strong>DMP Questions</strong></p>\r\n<p>Below is an overview of the questions you will need to address to complete your DMP. Click the \"Write Plan\" tab to begin responding to the questions.</p>","number":1,"template_id":3666,"created_at":"2022-02-28 20:12:26 UTC","updated_at":"2022-02-28 20:16:17 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"4189ab22-ee4a-4563-8e2e-2016f60969ba"},{"id":3692,"title":"PGD TS","description":"<p>Bienvenue dans le gabarit de PGD de l'&Eacute;cole de technologie sup&eacute;rieure.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>(Lien vers la page/guide sur la GDR de la biblio)</em></strong></p>","number":2,"template_id":3667,"created_at":"2022-03-01 19:22:30 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-11 14:10:03 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"3c30e0f7-9c77-4b00-a844-6918014f8db9"},{"id":3694,"title":"Portage Template for Qualitative Health Sciences Research","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This data management template is meant to be used by health sciences researchers conducting qualitative research on human subjects. It includes guidance on data management best practices beginning with data collection through to data sharing.</span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3668,"created_at":"2022-03-07 14:25:55 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-07 14:25:55 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"012fd11d-1c7c-424c-a883-6134132b8a82"},{"id":3695,"title":"University of Windsor Data Management Questions ","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3669,"created_at":"2022-03-22 13:14:01 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 13:14:01 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"a615218d-ffd0-4d4f-baed-341ee2076d77"},{"id":3696,"title":"test","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3670,"created_at":"2022-03-22 23:01:45 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-22 23:01:45 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"535d1792-8334-4e48-9889-6c8de4fe429c"},{"id":3697,"title":"Write Plan","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3671,"created_at":"2022-03-29 01:58:18 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-29 02:00:07 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"8b72d224-cfac-4728-be67-5292dc31e250"},{"id":3698,"title":"test","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3672,"created_at":"2022-03-31 21:27:55 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-31 21:27:55 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"535d1792-8334-4e48-9889-6c8de4fe429c"},{"id":3699,"title":"test","description":"","number":2,"template_id":3672,"created_at":"2022-03-31 21:42:37 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-31 21:42:37 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"11e47faf-b7ad-4cd7-b3ef-b4a0fa1c84c4"},{"id":3700,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3673,"created_at":"2022-03-31 21:45:52 UTC","updated_at":"2022-03-31 21:45:52 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3701,"title":"test","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3674,"created_at":"2022-04-04 16:27:24 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-04 16:27:24 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"829b36b3-435f-4f62-9d5e-65fc03a6ab25"},{"id":3702,"title":"Portage Data Management Questions","description":null,"number":1,"template_id":3675,"created_at":"2022-04-07 15:35:48 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-07 15:35:48 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"061b1c99-eb12-4550-be0b-445b1b77fe79"},{"id":3703,"title":"Phase 1","description":"<p>blurb of phase</p>","number":1,"template_id":3676,"created_at":"2022-04-07 15:40:37 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-04 21:34:45 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"1d89bda2-5c21-4993-9f68-39b25e1d787e"},{"id":3704,"title":"Ontario Agri-Food Innovation Alliance DMP creation","description":"<p>This is the template to use when developing a DMP as a requirement for Ontario Agri-Food Innovation Alliance funding.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Public Access to Your DMP</strong></p>\r\n<p>Increasing access and sharing of information is important for facilitating new agri-food and rural research and data analytics to inform decision-making. As such, the contents of this DMP may be made public. By completing this DMP, you are acknowledging that this information may be shared publicly. If you have any concerns please contact the U of G Library at <a href=\"mailto:lib.research@uoguelph.ca\">lib.research@uoguelph.ca</a>.</p>\r\n<p><strong>OMAFRA access to project data&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>As a recipient of funding through the Ontario Agri-Food Innovation Alliance, the Ontario Ministry of Agriculture, Food and Rural Affairs (OMAFRA) is entitled to request and be granted access to project data, including third-party data. Please contact Stacy Favrin, Senior Manager, OMAFRA/UofG Research Programs (<a href=\"mailto:favrinst@uoguelph.ca\">favrinst@uoguelph.ca</a>)&nbsp;for guidance before entering into a third-party agreement that may limit the Ministry's right to access data generated as part of this project.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Living Document</strong></p>\r\n<p>In most cases, DMPs are a condition of award. That said, DMPs are a living document that can be adjusted as necessary throughout the lifecycle of the project. Researchers are required to provide funders with updated information about their DMP if there are any changes. For Alliance projects, researchers are required to describe how the Data Management Plan has been implemented (if applicable) and if there any deviations from the proposed plan in the final report.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Clarity, Brevity and Accessibility</strong></p>\r\n<p>Please make your responses as clear and succinct as possible. For better accessibility, please avoid the use of tables.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Plan Details</strong></p>\r\n<p>On the previous tab, please ensure that you completed the fields as follows.</p>\r\n<p><em>Funder:</em> This should be \"Ontario Agri-Food Innovation Alliance.\"</p>\r\n<p><em>Grant Number:</em> This should be your Submission Number (e.g. UG-TI-2021-100000) and NOT the FRS Number.</p>\r\n<p><em>Project Abstract:</em> This can be copied and pasted from your application.</p>\r\n<p><em>ID:</em>&nbsp;This field is not relevant and does not need to be completed.</p>\r\n<p><strong>DMP Questions</strong></p>\r\n<p>Below is an overview of the questions you will need to address to complete your DMP. Click the \"Write Plan\" tab to begin responding to the questions.</p>","number":1,"template_id":3677,"created_at":"2022-04-11 18:39:31 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-11 18:40:56 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"4189ab22-ee4a-4563-8e2e-2016f60969ba"},{"id":3705,"title":"University of British Columbia Data Management Questions","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3678,"created_at":"2022-04-19 20:58:18 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-19 20:58:18 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"cb25d2e3-82f0-4e59-8c31-49622651e2d7"},{"id":3706,"title":"Food from Thought DMP creation","description":"<p>This is the template to use when developing a DMP as a requirement for Food from Thought funding.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Public Access to Your DMP</strong></p>\r\n<p>Increasing access and sharing of information is important for facilitating new agri-food and rural research and data analytics to inform decision-making. As such, the contents of this DMP may be made public. By completing this DMP, you are acknowledging that this information may be shared publicly. If you feel any information in your DMP should not be shared, please enter it in the \"confidential information\" section. If you have any concerns please contact the U of G Library at <a href=\"mailto:lib.research@uoguelph.ca\">lib.research@uoguelph.ca</a>.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Living Document</strong></p>\r\n<p>In most cases, DMPs are a condition of award. That said, DMPs are a living document that can be adjusted as necessary throughout the lifecycle of the project. Researchers are required to provide funders with updated information about their DMP if there are any changes. For Alliance projects, researchers are required to describe how the Data Management Plan has been implemented (if applicable) and if there any deviations from the proposed plan in the final report.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Clarity, Brevity and Accessibility</strong></p>\r\n<p>Please make your responses as clear and succinct as possible. For better accessibility, please avoid the use of tables.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Plan Details</strong></p>\r\n<p>On the previous tab, please ensure that you completed the fields as follows.</p>\r\n<p><em>Funder:</em> This should be \"Food from Thought.\"</p>\r\n<p><em>Grant Number:</em> This should be your Submission Number (e.g. UG-TI-2021-100000) and NOT the FRS Number.</p>\r\n<p><em>Project Abstract:</em> This can be copied and pasted from your application.</p>\r\n<p><em>ID:</em>&nbsp;This field is not relevant and does not need to be completed.</p>\r\n<p><strong>DMP Questions</strong></p>\r\n<p>Below is an overview of the questions you will need to address to complete your DMP. Click the \"Write Plan\" tab to begin responding to the questions.</p>","number":1,"template_id":3679,"created_at":"2022-04-22 14:03:41 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-22 14:03:42 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"4189ab22-ee4a-4563-8e2e-2016f60969ba"},{"id":3707,"title":"Phase 1: Data Management Plan for Grant Application","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&ldquo;Phase 1&rdquo; is for the documentation of DMP sections joined with a funding application. The headings documented in Phase&nbsp;1 are primarily aimed at producing a DMP to support research data management (RDM) budgeting for the research project.</span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3680,"created_at":"2022-04-25 17:33:52 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-25 17:33:52 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"05204d86-fc3a-4e00-a791-4701dd5042db"},{"id":3708,"title":"Phase 2: Data Management Plan for Project Development","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&ldquo;Phase 2&rdquo; may be considered once funding has been secured. The entire DMP is an evolving management document since the content of certain headings will only become clearer once the project is well underway.</span></p>","number":2,"template_id":3680,"created_at":"2022-04-25 17:33:52 UTC","updated_at":"2022-04-25 17:33:52 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"fce2cc8c-03bb-42b7-8e0e-471fb3d71a8e"},{"id":3709,"title":"Data management questions","description":"","number":1,"template_id":3682,"created_at":"2022-05-02 20:00:29 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-02 20:00:29 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"5685adbf-aaff-4abc-9463-8dd330561949"},{"id":3710,"title":"Portage Template for Open Science Workflows","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This template guides the writing of a research data management plan (DMP) with an open science/open scholarship workflow, which uses mixed social sciences research methods, producing quantitative as well as qualitative datasets. The questions emphasize data sharing and reuse throughout the project, not only at the final stage of publication. This DMP template will be most useful to researchers who are working in a multi-institutional partnership and who have already completed a funding application and an ethics review protocol.&nbsp; The DMP is a living document:</span> <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">don&rsquo;t forget to revisit your DMP throughout the research project to update or review your responses.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Not all of these questions will apply to all research projects. We encourage you to respond to as many as possible but ultimately, you and your team have to decide which questions and answers apply to your workflow. </span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3683,"created_at":"2022-05-03 16:34:05 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-03 16:34:05 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"e6951813-58f1-4b51-918d-5b29a744541d"},{"id":3711,"title":"Phase 2","description":"<p>blah blah blah</p>","number":2,"template_id":3676,"created_at":"2022-05-04 21:35:01 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-04 21:35:01 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"081d9676-4969-4b65-9734-20a0ac92afb6"},{"id":3712,"title":"Portage Template for Mixed Methods (Surveys & Qualitative Research)","description":"<p>This mixed methods data management plan template was developed for use within the Portage DMP Assistant and is meant to assist researchers conducting mixed methods research (e.g., surveys and qualitative interviews/focus groups) in developing high quality data management plans to support their research. The template consists of a number of categories, questions, and customized guidance that relate directly to mixed methods research.</p>","number":1,"template_id":3684,"created_at":"2022-05-05 15:04:34 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-05 15:04:34 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"1945d993-f3da-4a84-ad7f-ae2560946956"},{"id":3713,"title":"CRDCN Template for Accessing Data from Research Data Centres","description":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This template is for researchers who are doing RDC work using Statistics Canada data available in the RDC </span><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">only</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (i.e. there is no supplemental data, public use statistics, or any other information that complements the RDC work). If your work is being conducted in the RDC in concert with other data that you either intend to bring into the RDC or work on outside the RDC in parallel to your RDC work, then the RDC and External Analysis template should be completed.&nbsp;</span></p>","number":1,"template_id":3685,"created_at":"2022-05-05 15:04:51 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-05 15:04:51 UTC","modifiable":0,"versionable_id":"3d9e83e3-cfa8-463b-84a1-78bb0d7ba287"},{"id":3714,"title":"PGD TS","description":"<p>Bienvenue dans le gabarit de PGD de l'&Eacute;cole de technologie sup&eacute;rieure.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>(Lien vers la page/guide sur la GDR de la biblio)</em></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Votre plan de gestion de donn&eacute;es de recherche est un document &eacute;volutif : </em></strong>avant le d&eacute;but du projet, r&eacute;pondez au mieux de vos connaissances. Vous pourrez mettre &agrave; jour votre plan au besoin sir votre projet venait &agrave; changer.</p>","number":2,"template_id":3686,"created_at":"2022-05-11 16:17:27 UTC","updated_at":"2022-05-11 16:21:58 UTC","modifiable":1,"versionable_id":"3c30e0f7-9c77-4b00-a844-6918014f8db9"}]